      <section eId="sec_CHC-115">
        <num>CHC 115</num>
        <heading>115. Â Oath or affirmation in juvenile proceedings</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-115__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Witnesses shall swear or affirm to speak the truth and nothing but the truth.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-115__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A child witness need not be placed under oath or be required to make an affirmation if the court can otherwise assure that the child understands his obligation to speak the truth.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72637</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
